Project No: 0003
Project Name: Creating Multiple Apps in One Django Project

ðŸ“Œ Step 1: Create the Django Project
django-admin startproject HIETECH

ðŸ“Œ Step 2: Enter into the Project Directory
cd HIETECH

ðŸ“Œ Step 3: Create Django Applications
py manage.py startapp Students
py manage.py startapp Fees
py manage.py startapp Courses

Add them to INSTALLED_APPS inside HIETECH/settings.py:

INSTALLED_APPS = [
    'django.contrib.admin',
    'django.contrib.auth',
    'django.contrib.contenttypes',
    'django.contrib.sessions',
    'django.contrib.messages',
    'django.contrib.staticfiles',
    'Students',
    'Fees',
    'Courses',
]

ðŸ“Œ Step 4: Define View Functions for Each App
Students/views.py
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse

def student_view1(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Students section (view1)</h1>')

def student_view2(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Students section (view2)</h1>')

Fees/views.py
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse

def fees_view(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Fees section</h1>')

Courses/views.py
from django.shortcuts import HttpResponse

def course_view(request):
    return HttpResponse('<h1>Hello, you are in the Courses section</h1>')

ðŸ“Œ Step 5: Define URL Patterns
HIETECH/urls.py
from django.contrib import admin
from django.urls import path
from Students import views as v1
from Fees import views as v2
from Courses import views as v3

urlpatterns = [
    path('admin/', admin.site.urls),

    # Students App URLs
    path('students/view1/', v1.student_view1),
    path('students/view2/', v1.student_view2),

    # Fees App URL
    path('fees/', v2.fees_view),

    # Courses App URL
    path('courses/', v3.course_view),
]


ðŸ”‘ Note:
We use as v1, as v2, as v3 while importing views because each app has a views.py file.
Without aliasing, Python would overwrite the imports and cause conflicts.

ðŸ“Œ Step 6: Run Development Server and Test

Start server:
py manage.py runserver

Test the URLs in your browser:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/students/view1/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/students/view2/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/fees/
http://127.0.0.1:8000/courses/